	   <tr><td colspan=2>How did he figure out the pricing?<br>He did what I did...sat in EC on a Sunday night for a couple of hours a week and watch the prices fly by.&nbsp;&nbsp;You find out real quick what the market will and will not bear.  Sell higher than what you see and buy lower.  Don't base your prices on what some dusty web page says (all due respect Alla.), but prices fluctuate based on the availability of the item which is directly related to the age of the server.  On the older servers you will find a marked deflation over the newer servers.  People have had more time to get the high level loot and spread the wealth. A web page will give you a reasonable ball park figure but you won't make loads of money following the rules.  You need to push the envelope to make great profit.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
